title: Buckettes dominate match to claim sectional crown
text:
Buckettes dominate match to claim sectional crown Jake Furr , Reporter 9:32 p.m. EDT October 22, 2015 Three set victory punches ticket to district tournament in Willard Buy Photo Sarah Karl watches the ball during the Buckettes' three-set sectional championship victory on Thursday evening. (Photo: Jake Furr/ Telegraph-Forum) Buy Photo Story Highlights The Buckettes served the Trojans a three set defeat, 25-14, 25-13 and 25-23. Buckeye Central has not tasted defeat since Sept 29. The Trojans finish their season at 12-11. CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
NEW WASHINGTON - The Buckeye Central Buckettes are on a roll. 
There may not be many more words to describe the level of play that the Buckettes are showing as they picked up a sectional championship Thursday night. Buckeye Central hosted the championship match and welcomed the South Central Trojans rather rudely, serving them a three-set defeat, 25-14, 25-13 and 25-23. 
Buckeye Central has not tasted defeat since Sept. 29, when they hosted Northern 10 Champ Upper Sandusky. Since then, the Buckettes have dropped just three sets in route to a nine-game winning streak. 
“It is the start of our tournament run tonight so this title means a lot but we know it is just the beginning,” Reinhart said. 
The Buckettes started off in dominating fashion taking the first two sets without much of a fight. Claire Songer served for five points in the set and Bailey Agin recorded nine service points to pace the Buckeye Central effort. But it was defensively where the Buckettes shined. They allowed just four service points total in the first set by South Central, and four more in the second set. 
The third set saw a lapse in focus from Buckeye Central and the Trojans took advantage. They commanded most of the third set and even took a 20-18 lead at one point. But the Buckettes responded to take the two-point win and close out the match. 
“It is girls volleyball at its finest,” Reinhart added. “It is a roller coaster sometimes but they were able to go out and get the job done and at the end of the night that is all that matters.” Buy Photo 
South Central libero Hannah Vogel looks to return the ball during warmup before the sectional title game Thursday. (Photo: Jake Furr/ Telegraph-Forum) 
The Trojans finish their season at 12-11 and say goodbye to two seniors. The match was a representative of the type of season South Central has had. 
“It has been a fun season and we have grown so much from the beginning of the year to this point,” Trojan coach Sara Hohler said. “The season was kind of like the match tonight. We started really slow then started to pick it up towards the end.” 
Sarah Oney shined for the Trojans. The lefty sent down 10 kills on the evening. Lexie Adams contributed with six kills and four blocks. Madison Albert and Hannah Vogel both recorded four service points. 
“I am very proud of both of my seniors, Hannah Oney and Hannah Vogel, and we will miss them a lot,” Hohler added. “We have a lot of young girls and we learned something each night and it made us stronger as the season rolled along.” Buy Photo 
Buckette setter Addie Ackerman gets in a warm up before the sectional title game. (Photo: Jake Furr/Telegraph Forum) 
The Buckettes were led again by the three-headed monster of a front row in Jenna Karl, Jenna Delarber and Sarah Heydinger. Karl recorded 15 kills and five serving points including an ace. Delarber set down 13 kills and blocked two shots. It was Heydinger that made the hustle plays sending down 11 kills and blocking 10 shots including two blocks on the final point and smacked down her final kill to end the match. 
“Sarah gets after it. You tell her to give 100 percent and she will go out and give you 110. It is just the kind of player she is and we love her for it,” Reinhart added. 
Songer and Addie Ackerman finished with 10 serving points each, Ackerman chipped in four kills. Agin ended the evening with nine serving points and four aces. Erin Baldosser served for five points and recorded three kills. 
The Buckettes earned the Division IV Sectional title and a trip to Willard to face the winner of St. Paul and No. 2 ranked Old Fort. They will be back in action at 8 p.m. Tuesday for the district semifinals.
